Assessment of high-level copy loss. High-level loss is associated with a large negative log ratio between the ploidy at an indicated position and regional base ploidy. High-level loss is typically indicative of focal deletions. This term should be preferred in contrast to complete genomic deletion when a complete loss of all alleles at an indicated position cannot be reasonably assessed.
